# Implementation Plan - Fix Wiggle Test Drift

## Problem
The Wiggle Test fails to detect "Off Rope" status because the movement (StartX vs EndX) is too small (~2px) with the current 100ms press.
This causes the test to repeat multiple times, leading to cumulative drift (10px+) until the character grabs an adjacent rope.

## Solution
As suggested by the user, we will **increase the check duration**.
By pressing the Right key for **200ms** (instead of 100ms), the character will move more significantly (e.g., 4-5px).
This will reliably trigger the `DeltaX > 2.0f` threshold on the **first attempt**, causing the loop to exit immediately.
This prevents the cumulative drift and accidental rope grabbing.

We will also add a **Drift Guard** as a safety net.

## Proposed Changes

### Services/CharacterMovementController.cs

#### [MODIFY] ClimbRopeAsync
- **Wiggle Press Duration**:
  ```csharp
  SendKeyInput(VK_RIGHT, false);
  await Task.Delay(200, ct); // Increased from 100ms
  SendKeyInput(VK_RIGHT, true);
  ```
- **Drift Guard**:
  ```csharp
  // 如果 X 軸偏離起始點太多，強制中止 (防止吸到隔壁繩索)
  if (Math.Abs(currentPos.X - startPos.X) > 5.0f) { break; }
  ```

## Verification Plan
- **Scenario**: Character climbs rope.
- **Success**:
  - Wiggle Test checks ONCE.
  - Character moves ~4px right.
  - Loop exits.
  - No drift into adjacent ropes.
